{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id788bc19e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"271"},"text":"§ 271.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Findings and purposes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id788bc19f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Congress finds and declares the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The future well-being of the United States economy depends on a strong manufacturing base and requires continual improvements in manufacturing technology, quality control, and techniques for ensuring product reliability and cost-effectiveness.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Precise measurements, calibrations, and standards help United States industry and manufacturing concerns compete strongly in world markets.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Improvements in manufacturing and product technology depend on fundamental scientific and engineering research to develop (A) the precise and accurate measurement methods and measurement standards needed to improve quality and reliability, and (B) new technological processes by which such improved methods may be used in practice to improve manufacturing and to assist industry to transfer important laboratory discoveries into commercial products.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Scientific progress, public safety, and product compatibility and standardization also depend on the development of precise measurement methods, standards, and related basic technologies.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The National Bureau of Standards since its establishment has served as the Federal focal point in developing basic measurement standards and related technologies, has taken a lead role in stimulating cooperative work among private industrial organizations in efforts to surmount technological hurdles, and otherwise has been responsible for assisting in the improvement of industrial technology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Federal Government should maintain a national science, engineering, and technology laboratory which provides measurement methods, standards, and associated technologies and which aids United States companies in using new technologies to improve products and manufacturing processes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Such national laboratory also should serve industry, trade associations, State technology programs, labor organizations, professional societies, and educational institutions by disseminating information on new basic technologies including automated manufacturing processes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" It is the purpose of this chapter—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a8-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to rename the National Bureau of Standards as the National Institute of Standards and Technology and to modernize and restructure that agency to augment its unique ability to enhance the competitiveness of American industry while maintaining its traditional function as lead national laboratory for providing the measurements, calibrations, and quality assurance techniques which underpin United States commerce, technological progress, improved product reliability and manufacturing processes, and public safety;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1a9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to assist private sector initiatives to capitalize on advanced technology;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1aa-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to advance, through cooperative efforts among industries, universities, and government laboratories, promising research and development projects, which can be optimized by the private sector for commercial and industrial applications; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1ab-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s271/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to promote shared risks, accelerated development, and pooling of skills which will be necessary to strengthen America’s manufacturing industries.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id788bc1ac-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1901-03-03/ch872/s1"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1901, ch. 872, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/1449"},"text":"31 Stat. 1449","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/tV/s5111"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, title V, § 5111","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1427"},"text":"102 Stat. 1427","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id788bc1ad-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id788bc1ae-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id788bc1af-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsec. (b), was in the original “this Act” meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1901-03-03/ch872"},"text":"act Mar. 3, 1901, ch. 872","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/1449"},"text":"31 Stat. 1449","children":[],"tail":", known as the National Institute of Standards and Technology Act, which is classified generally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note below and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id788bc1b0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section read as follows: “The Office of Standard Weights and Measures shall be known as the National Bureau of Standards.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id788bc1b1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id788bc1b2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name; National Bureau of Standards Redesignated National Institute of Standards and Technology","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/s5115/c"},"text":"Section 5115(c) of Pub. L. 100–418","children":[],"tail":" provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/100/418/s5115/c"},"text":"“References in any other Federal law to the National Bureau of Standards shall be deemed to refer to the National Institute of Standards and Technology.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-03-04/ch141/s1"},"text":"Act Mar. 4, 1913, ch. 141, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/37/736"},"text":"37 Stat. 736","children":[],"tail":", created the Department of Labor and renamed the Department of Commerce and Labor as the Department of Commerce."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1b3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2023 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/23/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–23, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2023","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/137/125"},"text":"137 Stat. 125","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/118/23/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278u"},"text":"section 278u of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Testing, Rapid Analysis, and Narcotic Quality Research Act of 2023’ or the ‘TRANQ Research Act of 2023’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1b4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2020 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/207/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–207, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2020-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 2020","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/1001"},"text":"134 Stat. 1001","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/116/207/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting sections 278g–3a to 278g–3e of this title and provisions set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278g–3a"},"text":"section 278g–3a of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Internet of Things Cybersecurity Improvement Act of 2020’ or the ‘IoT Cybersecurity Improvement Act of 2020’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1b5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2018 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/236/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–236, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-14"},"text":"Aug. 14, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/2444"},"text":"132 Stat. 2444","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/115/236/s1"},"text":"“This Act [amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s272"},"text":"section 272 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and enacting provisions set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s272"},"text":"section 272 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘NIST Small Business Cybersecurity Act’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1b6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2017 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/329/tV/s501/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–329, title V, § 501(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/3023"},"text":"130 Stat. 3023","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/114/329/tV/s501/a"},"text":"“This section [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278k–1"},"text":"section 278k–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":", amending sections 278g–5, 278k, and 278"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":" of this title and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2199"},"text":"section 2199 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":", Armed Forces, and enacting provisions set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278k"},"text":"section 278k of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Manufacturing Extension Partnership Improvement Act’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1b7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2014 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/235/dB/tVII/s701"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–235, div. B, title VII, § 701","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/2220"},"text":"128 Stat. 2220","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/113/235/dB/tVII/s701"},"text":"“This title [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278s"},"text":"section 278s of this title","children":[],"tail":", amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s3722"},"text":"section 3722 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6622"},"text":"section 6622 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, enacting provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278s"},"text":"section 278s of this title","children":[],"tail":", and amending provisions set out as a note under this section] may be cited as the ‘Revitalize American Manufacturing and Innovation Act of 2014’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1b8-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2011 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/358/tVII/s701"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–358, title VII, § 701","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/4041"},"text":"124 Stat. 4041","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/111/358/tVII/s701"},"text":"“This title [amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278k"},"text":"section 278k of this title","children":[],"tail":" and enacting provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278k"},"text":"section 278k of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘NIST Grants for Energy Efficiency, New Job Opportunities, and Business Solutions Act of 2010’ or the ‘NIST GREEN JOBS Act of 2010’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1b9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2010 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/240/tIV/s4221"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–240, title IV, § 4221","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-09-27"},"text":"Sept. 27, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2596"},"text":"124 Stat. 2596","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/111/240/tIV/s4221"},"text":"“This part [part I (§§ 4221–4228) of subtitle B of title IV of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/240"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–240","children":[],"tail":", amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278k"},"text":"section 278k of this title","children":[],"tail":" and enacting provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278n"},"text":"section 278n of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Export Promotion Act of 2010’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1ba-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1998 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/309/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–309, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2935"},"text":"112 Stat. 2935","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/105/309/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting sections 278g–2a, 278p, and 1511e of this title, amending sections 278k, 3704, and 3711a of this title, enacting provisions set out as notes under sections 272 and 3711 of this title, and amending provisions set out as a note under this section] may be cited as the ‘Technology Administration Act of 1998’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1bb-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1992 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/245/tII/s201/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–245, title II, § 201(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-02-14"},"text":"Feb. 14, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/15"},"text":"106 Stat. 15","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/102/245/tII/s201/a"},"text":"“This title [amending sections 272 and 278n of this title and enacting provisions set out as notes under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s278n"},"text":"section 278n of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Emerging Technologies and Advanced Technology Program Amendments Act of 1991’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id788bc1bc-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1988 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/tV/s5101"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, title V, § 5101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"hre